From 450bb953130ce121033c0e8f4518378a8eef4d38 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 23:09:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Make structured decoding self-contained as mlx_lm.structured

The constraint machinery (request-parameter parsing, JSON schema/regex/
choice -> FSM compilation with caching, the per-request logits
processor, and mlx/numpy kernel backends) moves into the package as
mlx_lm.structured; the server's optional import now points at it. The
'structured' extra installs the one runtime dependency (outlines-core,
exact pin), so:

    pip install mlx-lm[structured]   # structured decoding enforced
    pip install mlx-lm               # behaves exactly like upstream

The test suite ships as tests/test_structured.py in upstream's unittest
style; spec tests run anywhere, FSM/processor/server-hook tests skip
without the extra (plus numpy/numba for the CPU test kernel).
STRUCTURED.md documents usage, caveats, and fork maintenance.
